{{Quote|EMPIRE HAS ORDERED A SYSTEMWIDE BLOCKADE TO SEIZE REBEL SPIES. INTERDICTOR CRUISERS EN ROUTE. ALL SHIPS THAT DEPART PRIOR TO IMPERIAL INSPECTION WILL BE NOTED.|Message from [[R2-D2]]|<ref name="Heir">''[[Heir to the Jedi]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Interdictor-class-Star-Destroyer-SWCT.png|thumb|right|300px|The ''Interdictor''&mdash;an ''Interdictor''-class heavy cruiser]]
An '''interdictor''', also called '''interdictor vessels''' or '''interdictor ships''', was the term for a type of [[starship]] employed by the [[Galactic Empire]] with the [[Gravity well projector|technology]] to generate a [[gravity]] [[Gravity well|well]], which had the capability to pull vessels out of [[hyperspace]] as well as preventing them from entering it. Interdictor vessels could be from various starship classes, ranging from [[frigate]]s to [[Star Destroyer]]s.

==Characteristics==
===Design===
[[File:InterdictorClassSD-EGTW.png|thumb|left|250px|An ''Interdictor''-class, characterized by its four spherical gravity well projectors.]]
An Interdictor vessel, or simply an Interdictor,<ref name="Tarkin">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref> was a type of [[warship]] that was capable of of blocking [[starship]]s from entering [[hyperspace]], or pulling them back into [[realspace]] using [[gravity well projector]]s that created artificial mass shadows.<ref name="Battles">''[[Star Wars: Battles that Changed the Galaxy]]''</ref> Gravity well projectors were circular in shape, with multiple Interdictor models being equipped with four projectors.<ref name="Ships of the Empire">{{EncyclopediaCite|Starships of the Empire and the Rebellion}}</ref> There were also multiple models of Interdictors within different starship classifications,<ref name="Tarkin" /> including [[Star Destroyer]],<ref name="BMF 20">{{BuildFalconCite|20|Starship Fact File}}</ref> [[heavy cruiser]],<ref name="Starships and Speeders">''[[Starships and Speeders]]''</ref> [[cruiser]],<ref name="Heir">''[[Heir to the Jedi]]''</ref> and [[frigate]].<ref name="Tarkin" />

===Models===
One of the earlier Interdictor models during the [[Imperial Era]] was the [[Detainer CC-2200]] cruiser, which was characterized by stubbed wing-ling lateral projections that housed four gravity well projectors. It was also designed with thick [[armor]] and a down-sloping bow and [[sublight engine]]s. The [[CC-7700 frigate]] shared these characteristics, but was an updated version of the older CC-2200.<ref name="Tarkin" /> The [[Immobilizer 418 cruiser]] was 600 [[meter]]s in length,<ref name="On the Front Lines">''[[Star Wars: On the Front Lines]]''</ref> and was equipped with four spherical gravity well projectors on its hull.<ref name="Tarkin" /> It also carried a complement of twenty-four [[TIE series|TIE fighter series]] craft<ref name="Heir" /> and was armed with twenty [[laser cannon]]s.<ref name="On the Front Lines" /> At the time of the Immobilizer's introduction, it was plagued with multiple technical issues despite its design being state-of-the-art.<ref name="Tarkin" />

[[File:Interdictor_Expansion_Pack_box_art.png|thumb|right|250px|An ''Interdictor''-class heavy cruiser.]]
The [[Interdictor-class heavy cruiser|''Interdictor''-class heavy cruiser]]<ref name="Starships and Speeders" /> was an evolution of the Immobilizer,<ref name="BMF 87">{{BuildFalconCite|87|Starship Fact File}}</ref> and had a delta wing-shaped design with four spherical gravity well projectors on its hull.<ref name="Stealth Strike">{{Rebels|Stealth Strike}}</ref> These projectors were vulnerable, with their destruction being capable of compromising the entire vessel.<ref name="Zero Hour">{{Rebels|Zero Hour}}</ref> Eventually, both the Immobilizer and ''Interdictor''-class cruiser were phased out of manufacturing and replaced by the [[Interdictor-class Star Destroyer|''Interdictor''-class]] [[Star Destroyer]]. Derived from the standard [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyer]], it measured at 1,600 meters in length<ref name="BMF 20" /> and was considered better protected.<ref name="Heir" />

==Role==
Interdictor vessels were deployed to generate interdiction fields to pull enemy ships out of hyperspace or prevent them from entering it to begin with. With these capabilities, Interdictors blockaded worlds, investigated suspicious [[hyperspace route]]s, and could form part of small [[battle group]]s<ref name="Starships and Speeders" /> or [[task force]]s<ref name="Tarkin" /> to support heavier lines of [[capital ship]]s while working with [[frigate]]s and [[starfighter]]s.<ref name="Starships and Speeders" /> Interdictors were placed in key locations along their patrol routes and capture ships from hyperspace to board them for inspection as well.<ref name="BMF 20" /> Interdictors could also act with an escort, but in times of desperation could operate without one.<ref name="Heir" />

==History==
===Berch Teller campaign===
[[File:Executrix-Trailer.png|thumb|left|250px|Interdictors supported a task force led by the ''Executrix'' (pictured).]]
For hundreds of [[Standard year|years]] the technology of gravity well projectors required a large, immobile power source. As such, Interdictor vessels could not be developed. During this period of time, gravity well technology was chiefly used to prevent travel near vital installations. However, this changed from research conducted during the [[Clone Wars]], which led to more efficient projectors, and Imperial field tests with gravity well projectors mounted onto a space going vessel.<ref name="Battles">''[[Star Wars: Battles that Changed the Galaxy]]''</ref> Following the Clone Wars and into the [[Imperial Era]], Interdictor vessels were used by the [[Imperial Navy]] to control hyperspace traffic, although the technology remained limited.<ref name="Tarkin" /> By [[14 BBY]],<ref name="Tarkin date">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of [[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']] to [[14 BBY]].</ref> during the [[Berch Teller campaign]], Imperial [[Vice Admiral]] [[Dodd Rancit]] suggested using Interdictors to pull the hijacked personal vessel of [[Moff]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin]], the ''[[Carrion Spike]]''. The [[Carrion Spike task force|task force]] used a trio of Interdictor vessels, including an older [[Detainer CC-2200]] [[cruiser]], a newer [[CC-7700 frigate]], and a newly developed and untested [[Immobilizer 418 cruiser]], which was developed for the [[Deep Core Security Zone]].<ref name="Tarkin" />

The [[task force]] activated their Interdictor vessels to capture the ''Carrion Spike'' [[corvette]] in the [[Obroa-skai system]], however the Interdictors failed and created an [[Incident in the Obroa-skai system|incident]] in which multiple civilian craft were pulled out of hyperspace, resulting in civilian casualties. The Immobilizer was dispatched back to the [[Corellian Engineering Corporation]] to correct its operational issues.<ref name="Tarkin" />

===A new cruiser===
[[File:G-8_Experimental_Projector_SWA.png|thumb|right|190px|''Interdictor''-class cruisers were an evolution of the Immobilizer 418s.]]
By [[4 BBY]],<ref name="SSDate">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of "[[Stealth Strike]]" to [[4 BBY]].</ref> a prototype [[Interdictor-class heavy cruiser|''Interdictor''-class heavy cruiser]], the [[Interdictor (Interdictor-class)|''Interdictor'']], was active in the [[Del Zennis system]] under the command of [[Admiral]] [[Brom Titus]] as it underwent examination.<ref name="Stealth Strike" /> The ''Interdictor''-class cruiser was an evolution of the Immobilizer 418 cruiser, and part of the [[Interdictor line|''Interdictor'' line]]<ref name="BMF 87" /> which included a combat refit, a suppression refit, and an experimental refit. The ''Interdictor'' operated alongside two other Interdictor cruisers, pulling a [[CR90 corvette]] out of hyperspace.<ref name="Armada">{{Armada|set=Interdictor Expansion Pack}}</ref> The ''Interdictor'' eventually captured the rebel corvette [[Liberator (CR90 corvette)|''Liberator'']] and its crew, including [[Commander]] [[Jun Sato]] and [[Ezra Bridger]]. During a [[Rescue on the Imperial Interdictor|rescue attempt]] by other [[Phoenix Cell]] members, the ''Interdictor'' and its escorting [[Arquitens-class command cruiser|''Arquitens''-class command cruisers]] were destroyed.<ref name="Stealth Strike" />

During the [[Lothal campaign]]'s culmination with the [[Battle of Atollon]]<ref name="Zero Hour" /> in [[2 BBY]],<ref name="Timelines">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''</ref> [[Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo|Thrawn]] deployed two ''Interdictor''-class cruisers along six [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyers]] of the [[Seventh Fleet (Galactic Empire)|7th Fleet]] to capture [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] leadership and destroy Phoenix Cell and [[Massassi Group]]. [[Kassius Konstantine's Interdictor|One Interdictor]] was commanded by [[Admiral]] [[Kassius Konstantine]], but was destroyed when Commander Sato sacrificed himself and his [[flagship]], the [[Quasar Fire-class cruiser-carrier|''Quasar Fire''-class cruiser-carrier]] ''[[Phoenix Nest]]'', by ramming the Interdictor. This created an opening for a rebel ship flown by [[Ezra Bridger]] to escape and warn others. The other cruiser, the ''[[Constrainer]]'', was destroyed when rebel [[Mandalorian]] reinforcements arrived from behind the 7th Fleet's formation, ambushing the ''Constrainer'' and destroying it with [[Missile|rocket]]s. With both Interdictors destroyed, the surviving rebel forces managed to escape the 7th Fleet's [[blockade]] of [[Atollon]].<ref name="Zero Hour" /> [[Standard year|Years]] prior to the [[Battle of Yavin]] [[Landonis Balthazar Calrissian|Lando Calrissian]] and [[L3-37]] were [[Ambush in the Halthor sector|ambushed]] in the [[Halthor sector]] by an Imperial interdictor as they delivered a shipment of [[All Terrain Defense Turret]] [[walker]]s. The ambush resulted in Calrissian and L3 losing the entirety of the cargo.<ref name="Commander">''[[Star Wars: Commander]]''</ref>

===Service during the Civil War===
[[File:Rebellion_in_the_Rim_cover_art.png|thumb|left|270px|''Interdictor''-class cruisers participated in multiple engagements of the Galactic Civil War]]
By [[1 BBY]],<ref name="VIDate">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of [[Vader Immortal: A Star Wars VR Series|''Vader Immortal'']] to [[1 BBY]].</ref> the [[Interdictor-class Star Destroyer|''Interdictor''-class]] [[Star Destroyer]], a variant of the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyer]],<ref name="BMF 20" /> was developed and in service to the [[Imperial Navy]]. One Interdictor Star Destroyer was commanded by Admiral [[Gable Karius]] above [[Mustafar]], capturing the [[Smuggler|smuggling]] ship ''[[Windfall]]''.<ref name="Vader Immortal">{{VaderImmortal|I}}</ref>

By [[0 ABY]],<ref name="0 ABY">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of ''[[Heir to the Jedi]]'' to [[0 ABY]].</ref> the Immobilizer 418 was no longer manufactured by the Empire due to its vulnerabilities, favoring to place the gravity well projectors on Star Destroyers instead as they were more difficult to destroy.<ref name="Heir">''[[Heir to the Jedi]]''</ref> Additionally, the Empire also cancelled production of the ''Interdictor''-class heavy cruiser, as they proved an easy target for rebels and again favored to place the projectors within Star Destroyers.<ref name="BMF 87" /> Despite this, Immobilizer 418 cruisers continued to be in service throughout [[the galaxy]] due to their abundance. One Immobilizer managed to pull [[Luke Skywalker]] out of hyperspace into the [[Daalang system]] after he managed to free a high-priority asset from the Imperial cause. However due to the ships frequent use against Alliance raiding groups, Luke Skywalker was able to form an attack strategy against the ship, ultimately destroying the vessel by splitting it in half with a [[Utheel Rockcrusher Compact Seismic Charge]].<ref name="Heir" />

[[File:VermillionAttacksInterdictor-HiddenEmpire1.png|thumb|right|260px|Crimson Dawn attacks an ''Interdictor''-class Star Destroyer.]]
In [[3 ABY]],<ref name="Timelines" /> [[Hunter Fleet's secondary strike force]] utilized an Interdictor during a [[battle near Malastare]] against the [[Eighth Division]] of the [[Rebel Alliance Navy|Alliance Navy]].<ref name="SW 1">[[Star Wars (2020) 1|''Star Wars'' (2020) 1]]</ref> Following the [[Syndicate War]] and other actions by [[Crimson Dawn]], an Interdictor Star Destroyer was attacked by the Crimson Dawn flagship ''[[Vermillion (Crimson Dawn)|Vermillion]]''.<ref name="Hidden Empire 1">{{SW|url=news/marvel-star-wars-hidden-empire-1-exclusive-preview|text=Qi'ra Challenges the Emperor in Marvel's ''Star Wars: Hidden Empire'' #1 &ndash; Exclusive Preview}}</ref> In [[4 ABY]],<ref name="Timelines" /> Interdictors formed the Imperial forces during the [[Battle of Endor]]. The Imperial ships hid behind [[Endor]] and moved into position to block an immediate escape while the fleet's Interdictors activated their generators to fully trap the Alliance fleet. Alliance starfighters outflanked the Imperial fleet and attacked the Interdictors and Imperial communications, and the [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station]] was eventually destroyed. As a result of the defeat, the surviving Imperial forces retreated.<ref name="Battles" />

[[File:Spectral-TheGhostShip.png|thumb|left|270px|The ''Spectral'' withdrew to Jakku, only to shortly be destroyed.]]
In [[5 ABY]],<ref name="Atlas">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]''</ref> the ''Interdictor''-class cruiser ''[[Spectral]]'' participated in the [[Battle of Fondor Shipyards]] against the [[New Republic]], and soon retreated to [[Jakku]]. In transit, one of its projectors was damaged by a Republic starfighter that managed to track the cruiser through hyperspace. Once in Jakku's orbit, the starfighter was brought in and the ship sabotaged, resulting in it crashing to Jakku's surface. Within moments, the [[New Republic Defense Fleet]] appeared<ref name="The Ghost Ship">{{StoryCite|story=The Ghost Ship|book=Star Wars Adventures: Destroyer Down}}</ref> and commenced the [[Battle of Jakku]] against the royalist Imperial forces, consisting of at least three naval battle groups.<ref name="Shadow Fall">''[[Shadow Fall: An Alphabet Squadron Novel]]''</ref> The Immobilizer ''[[Glaciate]]'' participated in the battle, during which it was infiltrated and captured by the [[New Republic]] operatives acting on [[General]] [[Carlist Rieekan]]'s orders. The battle resulted in the end of the [[Galactic Civil War]] and the final collapse of the Galactic Empire.<ref name="On the Front Lines" /> Many years later, scavengers from [[Niima Outpost]] sought to travel within the wreckage of the ''Spectral'' to plunder it.<ref name="The Ghost Ship" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Interdictor_Cruiser_Concept_Art.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Concept art of the ''Interdictor''-class cruiser in ''Star Wars Rebels''.]]
The concept of the Galactic Empire disabling vessels' hyperspace capabilities using Interdictor vessels first appeared in the ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' 1989 supplement [[Imperial Sourcebook]] and later used in ''[[Heir to the Empire]]'', a [[1991]] novel by [[Timothy Zahn]] that was the first in a [[Star Wars: The Thrawn Trilogy|trilogy]] featuring events set several years after the conclusion of the final film of the [[original trilogy]].<ref name="heire">''[[Heir to the Empire]]''</ref> While this trilogy is now considered part of the franchise known as [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] and no longer [[canon]],<ref name="End of EU">{{SW|url=news/the-legendary-star-wars-expanded-universe-turns-a-new-page|text=The Legendary Star Wars Expanded Universe Turns a New Page}}</ref> Interdictor vessels were featured in novels such as [[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']] and ''[[Heir to the Jedi]]'', which are considered part of a new continuity of canon.<ref name="Del Rey Relaunch">{{SW|url=news/disney-publishing-worldwide-and-random-house-announce-relaunch-of-star-wars-adult-fiction-line|text=Disney Publishing Worldwide and Random House Announce Relaunch of Star Wars Adult Fiction Line}}</ref>

